y can change the world.</p> <p>Michael talks about a researcher named Jonathan Gottschall, who studies the neuroscience behind stories. Jonathan says the constant firing of our neurons in response to fictional stimuli strengthens and refines the neural pathways that l... Do you give presentations or speak to clients? Want to illustrate your knowledge with better stories? To discover how to improve your stories, and your storytelling, I interview Michael Port. More About This Show The Social Media Marketing podcast is a... clean 51:56 Instagram Images: How to Stand Out on Instagram http://www.socialmediaexaminer.com/stand-out-on-instagram-peg-fitzpatrick/ Fri, 25 Sep 2015 10:00:11 +0000 http://www.socialmediaexaminer.com/?p=88961 <img width="150" height="78" src="http://www.socialmediaexaminer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/ms-podcast164-pegfitzpatrick-560-150x78.png" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="ms-podcast164-pegfitzpatrick-560" style="display: block; margin-bottom: 5px; clear:both;" srcset="http://www.socialmediaexaminer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/ms-podcast164-pegfitzpatrick-560-150x78.png 150w, http://www.socialmediaexaminer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/ms-podcast164-pegfitzpatrick-560.png 560w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /><p>Is your business on Instagram?</p> <p>Are you curious about what to post?</p> <p>To discover how to use images on Instagram, I interview Peg Fitzpatrick.<br /> More About This Show<br /> The Social Media Marketing podcast is an on-demand talk radio show from Social Media Examiner. It's designed to help busy marketers and business owners discover what works with social media marketing.</p> <p>In this episode I interview Peg Fitzpatrick, the co-author of The Art of Social Media: Power Tips for Power Users, which she wrote with Guy Kawasaki. She is also a social media strategist and an expert in visual marketing. Her clients include Motorola, Audi, Google, Virgin and others.</p> <p>Peg will 